  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\nThe \"global\" variable should be replaced with the standardized \"globalThis\"\r\nhttps://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/globalThis\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nrun `truffle develop`\r\n\r\ntruffle(develop)> let accounts = await web3.eth.getAccounts()\r\nUncaught ReferenceError: global is not defined\r\n    at evalmachine.<anonymous>:2:19\r\n\r\nglobal = globalThis\r\n\r\ntruffle(develop)> let accounts = await web3.eth.getAccounts()\r\nundefined\r\ntruffle(develop)> accounts\r\n[\r\n  '0xc30567b10027c99C6b22d578B9dEB85990b954bE',\r\n  '0xDCF9e2547212Ad204db456Af4B99a868e25293b0',\r\n  '0xaAC71A7B59C83A67bF1d616F411C1570fC58029D',\r\n  '0x7Aa3211e33D24eF45B42016d6c5B748657f477f2',\r\n  '0x3B2D7Cc5bA1f7B9d2a711C0A1cBab28Ef0cB7B46'\r\n]\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTruffle develop should work without using the \"global = globalThis\" workaround\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nTruffle develop returns the error \"global is not defined\"\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Windows\r\n* Ethereum client: Truffle develop\r\n\r\nTruffle v5.4.5 (core: 5.4.5)\r\nSolidity v0.5.16 (solc-js)\r\nNode v14.17.4\r\nWeb3.js v1.5.1\r\n\r\n",
